<h1 class="page-title">Latest Cybersecurity Insights</h1>

<div class="cyber-info">
    <div class="section">
        <h2>Ransomware Attacks</h2>
        <p>Ransomware attacks are on the rise, encrypting victims' data and demanding ransom for decryption keys. Protecting against such attacks requires robust backup strategies, updated anti-malware tools, and employee training to recognize phishing attempts.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
        <h2>Phishing Scams</h2>
        <p>Phishing scams trick users into providing sensitive information by mimicking legitimate requests. Strong email filters, user education, and two-factor authentication are critical defenses against these scams.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
        <h2>Data Breaches</h2>
        <p>Data breaches involve unauthorized access to data. Implementing strict access controls, using encryption, and regularly updating software can help mitigate the risk of data breaches.</p>
    </div>
</div>
